derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English (in the sense 'break wind quietly'): probably imitative (compare with fizz), but perhaps related to Middle English fist (see feisty). Current senses date from the 19th cent

entry.tran: 虎头蛇尾地结束;草草收场
entry.def: If something fizzles, it ends in a weak or disappointing way after starting off strongly.
